The Telegraph - Calcutta (Kolkata) | Business | Two more join RIL board 
                                                                                                               Two more join RIL board 
          OUR SPECIAL CORRESPONDENT                              
	Mumbai, Aug. 21: Mukesh Ambani-led Reliance Industries (RIL) has decided to expand its board of directors by appointing former Crisil chairman R. Ravimohan and head of RILs refining business P.M.S. Prasad as executive directors.        
	With these two appointments, the board of directors will expand to 14 members, with seven of them serving as independent directors.         
	Commenting on the appointments, RIL chairman and managing director Mukesh Ambani said, Ravi is undoubtedly one of the finest financial and risk management minds in the world, while Prasad has been an integral part of the growth story of Reliance and its achievements. I look forward to the contribution of these two talented professionals to take Reliance forward on an accelerated growth path.        
	Ravimohan recently wrapped up his assignments as chairman of Crisil and managing director and region head of Standard amp; Poors for South and South East Asia. He has been credited with Crisils growth in India. While Ravimohan is joining RIL as executive director, the exact nature of his portfolio in the countrys largest private sector company has not yet been disclosed.         
	Prasad has been with RIL for over 28 years and has held various positions within the company.                                                                                                                                       
